small
hours
of
the
morning
I
could
hear
the
clinking
of
his
test
tubes
which
told
me
that
he
was
still
engaged
in
his
malodorous
experiment.
In
the
early
dawn
I
woke
with
a
start,
and
was
surprised
to
find
him
standing
by
my
bedside,
clad
in
a
rude
sailor
dress
with
a
pea
jacket,
and
a
coarse
red
scarf
round
his
neck.
"I
am
off
down
the
river,
Watson,"
said
he.
"I
have
been
turning
it
over
in
my
mind,
and
I
can
see
only
one
way
out
of
it.
It
is
worth
trying,
at
all
events."
"Surely
I
can
come
with
